---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Best Scrabble Words for Triple Letter Squares — TLS Strategy"
  description="Master Triple Letter Score squares with the best words to land high-value tiles on TLS. From QI to JINX, maximize your TLS scoring potential. Free, no signup."
  keywords="triple letter score scrabble, best words tls, scrabble tls strategy, triple letter square words, high scoring tls plays"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Best Scrabble Words for Triple Letter Squares — TLS Strategy",
    "description": "Best words and strategies for maximizing Triple Letter Score squares in Scrabble.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-22",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/best-words-for-triple-letter-squares" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What tiles should you place on Triple Letter Score squares?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Always prioritize Z (10×3=30), Q (10×3=30), X (8×3=24), J (8×3=24), then K (5×3=15). A single Z on TLS gives you 30 points from one tile — equivalent to many entire words. Never waste a TLS on low-value tiles like E, A, or I." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best short words for hitting TLS in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "QI (11 pts, Q on TLS = 31), ZA (11 pts, Z on TLS = 31), JO (9 pts, J on TLS = 25), AX (9 pts, X on TLS = 25), and XI (9 pts, X on TLS = 25). Short words give you maximum control over tile placement on specific squares." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many Triple Letter Score squares are on a Scrabble board?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are 12 Triple Letter Score squares on a standard Scrabble board, positioned symmetrically. They're located at specific coordinates away from the center, making them accessible in the early-to-mid game when the board is still developing." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Best Scrabble Words for Triple Letter Squares — TLS Strategy</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-22">June 22, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Triple Letter Score squares multiply one tile's value by 3. The strategy is simple: place your highest-value tile on the TLS. Z on TLS = 30 points from one tile. Q on TLS = 30 points. X on TLS = 24 points. The trick is finding short, valid words that position your premium tile exactly on the TLS square — and that's what this guide covers.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TLS squares</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter multiplier</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">30 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Z on TLS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">24 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X on TLS</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Tile Value × TLS Impact</h2>
      <p>The difference between placing a high-value vs low-value tile on TLS is enormous.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Tile</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Base Value</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">On TLS</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Bonus Gained</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">Z</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">30</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">+20</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">Q</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">30</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">+20</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">X</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">+16</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">J</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">24</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">+16</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">K</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">+10</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">E</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-red-400">+2</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Best Short Words for TLS Targeting</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Short words (2-3 letters) are TLS weapons because you can <span class="text-white font-medium">precisely control tile placement</span>. A 2-letter word lets you choose exactly which tile lands on the TLS. With longer words, positioning depends on board layout and available hooks.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">QI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">Q on TLS = 31</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">Z on TLS = 31</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">J on TLS = 25</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">X on TLS = 25</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">XI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">X on TLS = 25</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">KA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">K on TLS = 16</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips for TLS Plays</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Count squares before playing:</span> Before committing to a word, count tile positions to verify your high-value letter actually lands on the TLS. Off by one square and you get zero bonus — a costly mistake.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays for double TLS hits:</span> Playing a word parallel to an existing one can sometimes hit two TLS squares in the same turn — once with your placed tile and once via a cross-word formed at the TLS position.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't open TLS for opponents:</span> If your play leaves a TLS square adjacent to a vowel, your opponent can play ZA, QI, or JO there next turn. Defensive awareness of which TLS squares you're exposing is critical.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JINX on TLS is devastating:</span> JINX scores 18 base. With J on TLS = 18 + 16 bonus = 34 total. With X on TLS instead = 18 + 16 = 34 total. Either way, JINX + TLS = 34+ points from 4 tiles.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/best-words-for-premium-squares/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Best Words for Premium Squares — complete premium strategy</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-worth-over-30-points/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Words Worth Over 30 Points — elite base-value scorers</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-words-for-premium-squares/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Words for Premium Squares</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-worth-over-30-points/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Worth Over 30 Points</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/words-with-x-in-the-middle/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words with X in the Middle</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
